      "The reward function can assign positive scores for correctly blocked malicious traffic and negative scores for false positives or added latency, guiding the agent toward an optimal long\u2011term strategy.",
      "The agent repeatedly observes a snapshot of the network environment, selects an action (such as allow, throttle, or block), and then receives a reward score based on how that action affected security and user experience.",
      "After the agent's policy stabilizes, it is typically deployed in shadow mode, where its recommendations are compared to human analysts' decisions before enabling full automation.",
      "The cycle consists of a one\u2011time training pass over historical data, after which the policy is frozen and no further interaction with simulated traffic is required.",
